<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1731] MarkupBuilder doesn&apos;t allow entities (like nbsp)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1731</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, there is no way to get this HTML code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;a:&amp;nbsp;b&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you try&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;span &apos;a:&amp;nbsp;b&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;you&apos;ll get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;a:&amp;amp;nbsp;b&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ie. the &quot;&amp;amp;&quot; gets escaped.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12813498">GROOVY-1731</key>
            <summary>MarkupBuilder doesn&apos;t allow entities (like nbsp)</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
