                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14462560" author="digulla" created="Wed, 14 Feb 2007 05:48:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple patch for the issue. Use it like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;builder.span builder.verbatim(&apos;&amp;nbsp;&apos;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new method MarkupBuilder.verbatim() wraps a string in a special object which protects the contents against escaping.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe a similar method can be used to fix the CDATA issue (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-267&quot; title=&quot;url(label: &amp;#39;test&amp;#39;) { CDATA(body) }&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-267&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-267&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14462624" author="tug" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2007 03:04:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please try to use the groovy.xml.Entity class for this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is what StreamingMarkupBuilder uses and it would be a bad idea for MarkupBuilder and StreamingMarkupBuilder to handle entities differently.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For this to work MarkupBuilder would have to understand the groovy.lang.Buildable interface and to provide an property called unescaped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would allow &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&quot;a${Entity.nbsp}b&quot;&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;span&amp;gt;unescaped &amp;lt;&amp;lt; &quot;a:&amp;nbsp;b&quot;&amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that you can put an nbsp into an HTML document with MarkupBuilder using the literal Unicode value of nbsp you just can&apos;t use an entity at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14462459" author="digulla" created="Mon, 19 Feb 2007 06:21:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m on Groovy 1.0 and there is no groovy.xml.Entity class, yet. If I find the time, I&apos;ll do a backport.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14477386" author="paulk" created="Sun, 22 Jul 2007 20:45:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just submitted a fix to HEAD. It doesn&apos;t provide hooks for getting to groovy.xml.Entity, I guess that is a potential additional enhancement. It does allow code like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;xml.p {
    em(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;Usually&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
    mkp.yield &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos; Hearts &amp;amp; Diamonds &apos;&lt;/span&gt;
    b(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;beats&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
    mkp.yieldUnescaped &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos; Spades &amp;amp;amp; Clubs&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix should be enough to allow you to manually add:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;span {
    mkp.yieldUnescaped &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;a:&amp;amp;nbsp;b&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463198" author="paulk" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2007 20:26:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No further feedback, assuming fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
